<s docid="AP900802-0135" num="56" wdcount="29"> For its part, the provisional government announced through Baghdad's official Iraqi News Agency that it was dissolving parliament and would hold ``free and honest elections'' at a future date.</s>
<s docid="AP900802-0135" num="57" wdcount="20"> The Iraqi forces were led by the elite Republican Guard, which did the brunt of fighting in the Iran-Iraq war.</s>
<s docid="AP900802-0135" num="58" wdcount="15"> Troops set up roadblocks at major intersections and shot at cars that did not stop.</s>
